\b \cf2 \cb3 Etymology
\f2\b0 \cf0 \cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0 \cf2 \cb3 There is no consensus on the etymology of 
\i angama
\i0 . One theory decomposes 
\i angama
\i0  into *
\i an
\i0  (possibly meaning mother) and *
\i gama
\i0  (possibly a diminutive suffix). Another theory relates 
\i angama
\i0  to "elder sister" (
\i angw\uc0\u257 
\i0  in Okinawan). Some argue that it might mean "disguise of a mask."\cf2 \cb1 \
