\i0 , depending on regional variants, and they are surrounded by male and female dancers. "Shichigwachi Nenbutsu" (
\f1 \'c6\'df\'d4\'c2\'c4\'ee\'81\'96
\f0 ), "K\uc0\u333 K\u333  Nenbutsu" (
\f1 \'d0\'a2\'d0\'d0\'c4\'ee\'81\'96
\f0 ) and "
\i Chonjon
\i0  Nenbutsu" (
\f1 \'d6\'d9\'ed\'98\'c4\'ee\'81\'96
\f0 ) were mainly sung.\cf2 \cb3 \
